Frank, do you put the recorder in the echo chamber, or outside it?  Thanks!

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Sumption &lt;purplealiengirl@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;  No, the echo chamber is not needed, but it does seem to add something, or
&gt; allow some other levels access. For the past couple years I&#39;ve been using
&gt; mostly what I call direct mode, or no echo chamber. When I use an aluminum
&gt; foil chamber I seem to get more ET types, and that&#39;s what I used to get &quot;we
&gt; come from the 6th planet&quot; years ago.
&gt; 
&gt;  A very large echo chamber can have a dramatic effect, like 12 inches
&gt; square, and 4 feet long. I made one that size out of MDF board and lined it
&gt; wiht aluminum foil, the voices were so demonic sounding that I took it
&gt; apart. Later I found that if something works, you tend to get the negative
&gt; guys to try to scare you away from it.
&gt; 
&gt;  F-S
